    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5259" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέρδος</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εος</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">gain, profit; shrewd counsel</span>, esp.
          pl., <i><span class="en">Il. 23.515</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; κέρδεα ἐπίστασθαι, εἰδέναι</span>, to be
          ‘versed in cunning arts,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 23.322</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; νωμᾶν ἐνὶ φρεσί</span>, ‘devise clever
          counsels,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 18.216</span></i>; in bad sense,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 2.88</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 23.217</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
